President Obama has nominated Ronald Lee Miller to serve as the United States Marshal for the District of Kansas. Miller is currently the Chief of Police for the City of Topeka, a position he has held since 2006. He has had a long career in law enforcement, working for the Kansas City, Kansas Police Department from 1972 to 2006, eventually becoming Chief of Police from 2000 to 2006. Miller has also worked as a consultant for the Police Foundation and the Civil Rights Division of the United States Department of Justice. He holds a Master's degree from Wichita State University and a Bachelor's degree from the University of Central Missouri. President Obama commended Miller for his dedication to protecting citizens and his pursuit of justice, and is honored to nominate him for this position.